{{NvidiaGPU | name = NVIDIA GeForce 9 Series | image = [[Image:GeForce newlogo.png|GeForce logo]] | codename = G92a/b, G94a/b, G96a/b, G98 | created = 2008 | entry = 9100 (IGP, OEM), 9200 (IGP, OEM), 9300GS/GT (IGP), 9300GE, 9400GS/GT (both integrated and discrete variants), 9500GS | midrange = 9500GT, 9600GT/GSO | highend = 9800GT/GTX/GTX+ | d3dversion = [[Direct3D|D3D]] 10.0, Model 4.0 | openglversion = 3.3 | version = 266.58}} The '''GeForce 9 Series''' is the ninth generation of [[NVIDIA|NVIDIA's]] [[GeForce]] series of [[graphics processing unit]]s, the first of which was released on February 21, 2008. == GeForce 9300 Series == ===Geforce 9300GE === *65nm G98 GPU *PCI-E x16 *64 Bit Bus Width *4 ROP, 8 Unified Shaders *540 MHz Core Clock *256 MB DDR2, 400 MHZ Memory Clock *1300 MHZ Shader Clock *5.1 G Texture/s fillrate *7.6 GB/s Memory bandwidth *Supports DirectX 10, SM 4.0 == GeForce 9400 Series == ===GeForce 9400 GT=== On August 27, 2008 the GeForce 9400 GT was officially launched. *65 nm G96 GPU *16 Stream Processors *550 MHz core, with a 1350 MHz [[Unified shader model|unified shader]] clock *4.4 billion texels/s fillrate *256 MB/512 MB/1024 MB 800 MHz [[DDR2 SDRAM|DDR2]] or 256 MB 1600 MHz [[GDDR3]],[http://www.galaxytech.com/news_details.asp?id=221], "Galaxy Technology 9400GT news page", August 27, 2008. (Accessed August 28, 2008.) both with a 128-bit memory bus *12.8 GB/s memory bandwidth for boards configured with DDR2 800 MHz memory *Support DirectX 10, Shader Model 4.0, [[OpenGL#OpenGL_3.3|OpenGL 3.3]], and PCI-Express 2.0 *Supports 2nd generation [[Nvidia PureVideo|PureVideo HD]] technology with partial VC1 decoding and [[Scalable Link Interface#Hybrid SLI|HybridPower]] technology.[http://www.firingsquad.com/news/newsarticle.asp?searchid=20798], "Firing Squad", August 26, 2008. (Accessed August 26, 2008.)[http://www.geeks3d.com/?p=1151 "Geforce 9200GS/9400GT reviewed"], "Geeks of 3D", August 27, 2008.[http://forums.techarp.com/news/24581-axle-nvidia-geforce-9400gt-gddr2-launched.html], "TechARP forums", August 27, 2008. *Minimum of 300 watt power supply supported == GeForce 9500 Series == ===GeForce 9500 GT=== [[File:Gigabyte NVIDIA GeForce 9500 GT.JPG|thumb|GeForce 9500 GT]] On July 29, 2008 the GeForce 9500 GT was officially launched. *65 nm G96 GPU *32 Stream Processors. *550 MHz core, with a 1400 MHz [[Unified shader model|unified shader]] clock. *8.8 billion texels/s fillrate. *256 MB/512 MB/1024 MB 1,600 MHz [[GDDR3]] memory or 256 MB/512 MB 1,000 MHz [[GDDR2]] memory, both with a 128-bit memory bus. *25.6 GB/s memory bandwidth for boards configured with GDDR3 800 MHz memory. *Support DirectX 10, Shader Model 4.0, OpenGL 3.3, and PCI-Express 2.0. *Supports 2nd generation [[Nvidia PureVideo|PureVideo HD]] technology with partial VC1 decoding.[http://vr-zone.com/articles/albatron-plans-9500gt-pcie-x1-card-for-sff-htpc/6707.html?doc=6707 Albatron Plans 9500GT PCIe x1 Card For SFF/HTPC], VR-Zone[http://www.bit-tech.net/news/industry/2008/08/19/zotac-unleashes-silent-geforce-9500-gt/1 ZOTAC Unleashes Silent GeForce 9500 GT], bit-tech.net *NVIDIA SLI - ready technology *HDMI technology Support ===GeForce 9500 GS=== The 9500 GS is an OEM card that's based on the 9500 GT but geared towards the mainstream audience. *65 nm G96 GPU *32 Stream Processors. *8 Raster Operations (ROP) units *550 MHz Core, with a 1375 MHz [[Unified shader model|unified shader]] clock. *8.8 billion texels/s Fillrate. *128 MB 1000 MHz [[DDR2 SDRAM|DDR2]] memory with a 128-bit memory bus. *16.0 GB/s memory bandwidth. *Supports DirectX 10, Shader Model 4.0, OpenGL 3.3, and PCI-Express 2.0 *Supports 2nd generation [[Nvidia PureVideo|PureVideo HD]] technology with partial VC1 decoding. *NVIDIA SLI - ready technology *HDMI technology Support == GeForce 9600 Series == === GeForce 9600 GT === [[File:Geforce 9600 GT GE.JPG|thumb|GeForce 9600 GT with cooler removed]] On February 21, 2008 the GeForce 9600 GT was officially launched. It was an upgrade of 8600 GTS. *65 nm G94 GPU. *64 Stream Processors. *16 Raster Operation(ROP) units, 32 Texture Address(TA)/Texture Filter(TF) units. *20.8 billion texels/s fillrate. *650 MHz core clock, with a 1625 MHz unified shader clock. *1008 MHz memory, 2016 MHz data rate, with a 256-bit memory interface. *512MB of GDDR3 or DDR2 memory. *57.6 GB/s memory bandwidth for boards configured with GDDR3 1800 MHz memory. *505M transistor count *DirectX 10.0, Shader Model 4.0, OpenGL 3.3, and PCI-Express 2.0.{{zh icon}} [http://www.pconline.com.cn/diy/graphics/reviews/0801/1205247_1.html "é¢åæ­£å¼åå¸1ä¸ªæ!G94æ ¸å¿GeForce 9600GTå¨çé¦åè¯æµ"], "pconline", January 14, 2008. (Accessed January 14, 2008.) *Supports 2nd generation [[Nvidia PureVideo|PureVideo HD]] technology with partial VC1 decoding. *Is compatible with [[High-bandwidth Digital Content Protection|HDCP]], but the implementation will depend on the manufacturer. *Supports [[CUDA]] and the Quantum Effects physics processing engine. *Almost double the performance of the previous Nvidia mid-range card, the GeForce 8600GTS. === GeForce 9600 GSO === The GeForce 9600 GSO was essentially a renamed 8800 GS. This tactic has been seen before in products such as the GeForce 7900 GTO to clear unsold stock when it is made obsolete by the next generation. Just like the 8800 GS, the 9600 GSO features 96 stream processors, a 550 MHz core clock with shaders clocked at 1,375 MHz, and either 384 or 768MB memory clocked at 800 MHz on a 192-bit memory bus. Some manufacturers have mistakenly listed some of their 768MB models that have 96 stream processors as being based on the G94 Chip, rather than the G92.http://www.nvidia.com/object/product_geforce_9600_gso_us.html === GeForce 9600 GSO 512 === After clearing the old 8800 GS stock, Nvidia revised the specification with a new core, and 512 MB of memory clocked at 900 MHz on a 256-bit bus.http://www.nvidia.com/object/product_geforce_9600_gso_512_us.html For these cards the number of stream processors is halved to 48, with the core frequency increased to 650 MHz and the shader frequency increased to 1625 MHz. Some of these cards have 1024 megabytes of memory while still being a 512 model. The revised version is considered inferior in performance to the old version. === GeForce 9600 GTX === XFX released a 9600 GTX based on the G92 Chip featuring 96 stream processors, a 580Mhz core clock, 1450Mhz shaders and 512MB of GDDR3 running at 1400Mhz on a 256 bit bus. Other than clock speeds, it is functionally the desktop equivalent version of the 9800M GT. http://www.xfxforce.com/en-us/products/graphiccards/9series/9600GTX.aspx#2 == GeForce 9800 Series == The GeForce 9800 series contains the GX2 (dual GPU), GTX, GTX+ and GT variants.[http://www.nvidia.com/object/geforce_family.html nVidia GeForce Family], retrieved February 25, 2008 ===GeForce 9800 GX2=== [[Image:NVIDIA GeForce 9800 GX2.png|thumb|NVIDIA GeForce 9800 GX2]] On March 18, 2008 the GeForce 9800 GX2 was officially launched. The '''GeForce 9800 GX2''' has the following specifications:.[http://enthusiast.hardocp.com/article.html?art=MTQzOSwxLCxoZW50aHVzaWFzdA== "GeForce 9800 GX2 Exclusive Pics & Specs"], "Hard OCP", January 3, 2008. (Accessed January 4, 2008.)[http://www.tomshardware.com/2008/01/05/exclusive_nvidia_geforce_9800gx2/ "Exclusive: Nvidia GeForce 9800GX2"], "Tom's Hardware", January 4, 2010. (Accessed January 4, 2008.) *Dual [[Printed Circuit Board|PCB]]s, dual GPU design *197 W power consumption.[http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/03/18/AR2008031800873.html Nvidia's GeForce 9800 GX2 Launches], "Washington Post", March 18, 2008. (Accessed February 15, 2008.) *Two [[65nm]] process GPUs, with 256 total Stream Processors (128 per PCB).[http://www.fudzilla.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=5654&Itemid=1 "Geforce 9800GX2 has two G92GTS"], "Fudzilla", February 11, 2008. (Accessed March 19, 2008.) *Supports Quad [[Scalable Link Interface|SLI]]. *Power of Two underclocked GeForce 8800 GTS 512(G92) video cards in SLI Mode *1 [[gibibyte|GiB]] (512 [[mebibyte|MiB]] per PCB) memory framebuffer. *Supports DirectX 10, Shader Model 4, OpenGL 3.3, and PCI-Express 2.0. *Supports 2nd generation [[Nvidia PureVideo|PureVideo HD]] technology with partial VC1 decoding. *Outputs include two [[Digital Visual Interface|DVI]] ports, an [[High-Definition Multimedia Interface|HDMI]] output, and S/PDIF in connector on-board for routing audio through the HDMI cable.[http://www.tweaktown.com/news/8961/index.html "GeForce 9600GT to include DisplayPort"], "TweakTown", February 14, 2008. (Accessed February 15, 2008.) *An 8-pin and a 6-pin power connector. *Clocks (Core/Shader/Memory): 600 MHz/1500 MHz/2000 MHz [http://www.hardware.no/artikler/dette_er_geforce_9800_gx2/48692 "NVIDIA GeForce 9800M GX2"], "Hardware.no". (Accessed February 18, 2008 *256-bit memory interface *128 GB/s memory bandwidth *Release date: March 18, 2008 *Launch price of $599.[http://www.amazon.com/dp/B0015U7YCG "Amazon.com: EVGA 9800 gx2"], "Amazon", March 18, 2008. (Accessed March 18, 2008.) ===GeForce 9800 GTX=== On April 1, 2008 the GeForce 9800 GTX was officially launched. It was basically an 8800 GTS 512MB with two SLI connectors, higher clock speeds, and support for Nvidia Hybrid Power, a technology that allows the discrete GPU to shut off during non resource intensive applications, and instead use the integrated GPU. With these extra features though, a high price came too. Taken from an eVGA specification sheet:[http://www.evga.com/products/pdf/512-P3-N871-AR.pdf "eVGA GeForce 9800 GTX Product Specification Sheet"], "eVGA Spec Sheet". (Accessed March 17, 2008.) *128 Stream Processors. *Clocks (Core/Shader/Memory): 675 MHz/1688 MHz/2200 MHz *256-bit memory interface. *512 MB of GDDR3 memory. *70.4 GB/s memory bandwidth *Texture Fill Rate of 43.2 (billion/s). *DirectX 10, Shader Model 4.0, OpenGL 3.3, and PCI-Express 2.0. *Supports 2nd generation [[Nvidia PureVideo|PureVideo HD]] technology with partial VC1 decoding. *Outputs include two DVI ports, an HDMI output(Using Nvidia DVI to HDMI adapter(included)), and S/PDIF in connector on-board for routing audio through the HDMI cable. *Release date was 2008-04-01.[http://www.fudzilla.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=6415&Itemid=1 "9800GTX pushed to April"], "Fudzilla". (Accessed March 21, 2008.) *Launch Price of $349.[http://www.fudzilla.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=6417&Itemid=1 "9800GTX listed for $350"], "Fudzilla". (Accessed March 21, 2008.) In July 2008 Nvidia released a refresh of the 9800 GTX: the '''9800 GTX+''' (55 nm manufacturing process). It has faster core (738 MHz) and shader (1836 MHz) clocks. Since March 2009 this design is manufactured as [[GeForce_200_Series#Technical_summary|GeForce GTS 250]]. ===GeForce 9800 GT=== The 9800GT is identical to an [[GeForce_8_Series#8800_GT|8800GT]], although some are being manufactured using a 55 nm technology instead of the 65 nm first debuted on the 8800GT.[http://www.hexus.net/content/item.php?item=14656&page=2 9800GT Product Specs.], "Hexus.net" (Retrieved November 9, 2008.) Newer (55 nm) version supports [[Hybrid SLI|HybridPower]] while 65 nm doesn't. The G92 design has been later relabeled for a second time and sold as [[GeForce_200_Series#Technical summary|GTS 250]] and later, a third time only by OEMs as the [[GeForce_300_Series#Technical summary|GT 330]]. ASUSTeK have released a 9800GT with Tri-SLI support.[http://www.asus.com/products.aspx?l1=2&l2=6&l3=656&l4=0&model=2423&modelmenu=1 Tri-SLI compatible 9800GT] (Retrieved November 9, 2008.) Taken from the Nvidia product detail page.[http://www.nvidia.com/object/product_geforce_9800gt_us.html "GeForce 9800GT Product Specifications"], "nVidia Product Specifications".
